OL,3,CThe cancer side effects many men are
OL,4,Ctoo embarrassed to talk about
OL,6,F"I want people to treat me normally. I
OL,7,Fnever wanted to be the guy with cancer.
OL,9,FA new survey from expert cancer
OL,10,Fsupport charity Maggie's reveals men
OL,11,Fcan feel guilt and embarrassment
OL,12,Ffollowing a cancer diagnosis.
OL,14,FThe survey found 17 % of all 500 men
OL,15,Fwith cancer polled initially felt
OL,16,Fembarrassed about their diagnosis
OL,17,Fwhile 41% of men felt anxious.
OL,19,F12% said they felt guilty after their
OL,20,Fdiagnosis and 23% said they felt
OL,21,Floneliness.
